forts, refigured marginal locales like Flushing Meadows and the shores of Long Island Sound and the East River in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries. The result is a synthesis of planning history, environmental history, and urban history that recasts the story of New York as we know it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCities and townszNew York (State)zNew YorkxGrowth. 0aCity planningzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy19th century. 0aCity planningzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aGreater New York.  aRobert Moses.  acity planning.  aenvironment.  agovernment.  asuburbanization.  aurbanization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226613161423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226613161/original  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019